modules.description: This module implements interval creation and manipulation using floating-point bounds and associated values. It provides functions to construct intervals from bounds and values, convert tuples to intervals, and extract tuple representations from intervals. Useful for applications like time-range scheduling, numerical range queries, or segment-based data processing.

This module provides an interval tree data structure that efficiently finds intervals containing a given point, with support for building trees from lists of intervals or triplets of bounds and values. It includes operations to construct, query, and manipulate intervals using floating-point bounds and associated values, enabling efficient range-based lookups. The tree can be used to find all intervals overlapping a specific time or numerical value, such as identifying conflicting time slots in scheduling or overlapping DNA segments in genomics. Submodule functions allow direct interval creation and conversion from tuples, supporting flexible data input and extraction for numerical range queries and segment-based processing.
